#: Game.Levels.SetOpsWorld.L13_DeMorgan
msgid "# De Morgan's Law for Sets\n"
"\n"
"One of the most important identities in set theory is **De Morgan's law**:\n"
"\n"
"В§0\n"
"\n"
"In words: the complement of a union equals the intersection of the\n"
"complements. An element is outside В§1 if and only if it is\n"
"outside both В§2 and В§3.\n"
"\n"
"You already proved the В§4 direction in Level 11 using В§5.\n"
"Now you must prove the full **equality** вҖ” both directions.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. В§6 вҖ” reduce to membership biconditional\n"
"2. В§7 вҖ” split the В§8 into forward (В§9) and backward (В§10)\n"
"3. **Forward** (В§11): Given В§12, prove В§13.\n"
"   Use В§14 and В§15 as in Level 11.\n"
"4. **Backward** (В§16): Given В§17, prove В§18.\n"
"   Destructure the hypothesis, introduce the union assumption,\n"
"   then case-split.\n"
"\n"
"This is the longest proof in the world so far. Take it step by step вҖ”\n"
"each individual step is familiar from earlier levels."
msgstr ""

