#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld.L13_GaloisConnection
msgid "You proved В§0 -- the Galois connection!\n"
"\n"
"**Why this matters**: The Galois connection lets you switch between\n"
"two viewpoints:\n"
"- **Image viewpoint**: \"every output from В§1 lands in В§2\"\n"
"- **Preimage viewpoint**: \"every element of В§3 maps into В§4\"\n"
"\n"
"The preimage viewpoint is often simpler because preimage membership\n"
"is just В§5 -- no existential, no witness. So when you need\n"
"to prove В§6, you can rewrite with В§7\n"
"to get the easier goal В§8.\n"
"\n"
"**The proof structure**:\n"
"- **Forward**: Start with В§9, build В§10 (construct\n"
"  the witness В§11), then apply the subset hypothesis\n"
"- **Backward**: Start with В§12, destructure to get В§13,\n"
"  then apply the subset hypothesis directly (no construction needed!)\n"
"\n"
"The backward direction is shorter because preimage is simpler than image.\n"
"\n"
"**The general definition**: Two monotone functions В§14 and\n"
"В§15 between ordered sets form a **Galois connection** when\n"
"В§16 for all В§17. Here В§18 (image) and\n"
"В§19 (preimage), with В§20 as the order. This pattern appears\n"
"whenever two operations are \"adjoint\" to each other -- you will\n"
"study Galois connections formally in Orders and Lattices.\n"
"\n"
"The library name is В§21."
msgstr ""

