msgid "# Chaining Subsets\n"
"\n"
"If В§0 and В§1, then В§2. This is\n"
"**transitivity** of the subset relation.\n"
"\n"
"In Level 6, you learned that a subset hypothesis В§3 acts as\n"
"a function: given a proof that В§4, it returns a proof that\n"
"В§5. Now you will **chain** two such function applications to\n"
"prove transitivity.\n"
"\n"
"There are two natural proof strategies:\n"
"\n"
"**Backward (with В§6)**: Start from the goal В§7 and work\n"
"backward. В§8 reduces the goal to В§9 (since В§10 says\n"
"\"if in В§11, then in В§12\"). Then В§13 reduces to В§14.\n"
"Then В§15 closes it.\n"
"\n"
"**Forward (with В§16)**: Start from В§17 and work forward.\n"
"В§18 gives В§19. Then\n"
"В§20 gives В§21. Then В§22.\n"
"\n"
"Try the backward approach вҖ” it is shorter and builds your В§23 skills."
msgstr ""

