msgid "You proved В§0.\n"
"\n"
"The proof used ONE witness В§1 from В§2, which belongs to\n"
"ALL В§3 simultaneously. For each index В§4, the same В§5 serves as\n"
"witness for В§6.\n"
"\n"
"**Why equality fails**: The reverse direction would require: given\n"
"separate witnesses В§7 for each В§8 (all with В§9),\n"
"finding a single В§10 with В§11. If В§12 is not\n"
"injective, the witnesses В§13 might all be different, and no single\n"
"В§14 might be in every В§15.\n"
"\n"
"**Concrete counterexample**: Let В§16, with В§17\n"
"and В§18 (indexed by В§19). Then В§20\n"
"(no element is in both), so В§21. But\n"
"В§22 and В§23, so\n"
"В§24. The strict inclusion\n"
"В§25 shows equality fails. The outputs В§26\n"
"and В§27 appear in every В§28 via DIFFERENT witnesses, but no\n"
"single witness belongs to every В§29.\n"
"\n"
"**The pattern**: This is the indexed version of the same phenomenon:\n"
"\n"
"| Operation | Preimage | Image |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| Binary В§30 | = | only \\\\subseteq |\n"
"| Indexed В§31 | = | only \\\\subseteq |\n"
"| Binary В§32 | = | = |\n"
"| Indexed В§33 | = | = |\n"
"\n"
"The next level proves the indexed union case вҖ” the В§34 in the last\n"
"row. Image preserves ALL unions (binary and indexed) as equalities,\n"
"but only \\\\subseteq for intersections.\n"
"\n"
"The library name is В§35."
msgstr ""

