#: Game.Levels.SetOpsWorld.L01_UnionMembership
msgid "# Set Operations: Union\n"
"\n"
"In the last two worlds, you learned that sets are predicates and that\n"
"subset/equality proofs reduce to propositional logic. Now you will learn\n"
"the **set operations** вҖ” union, intersection, complement, and difference вҖ”\n"
"and see that each one corresponds to a logical connective.\n"
"\n"
"The first operation is **union**. The union of two sets В§0 and В§1,\n"
"written В§2, contains every element that belongs to В§3 **or** В§4\n"
"(or both):\n"
"\n"
"В§5\n"
"\n"
"So union IS disjunction. When you need to prove В§6, you are\n"
"proving a disjunction. You choose which side to prove using two new\n"
"tactics:\n"
"\n"
"- В§7 вҖ” reduces the goal to the left disjunct (В§8)\n"
"- В§9 вҖ” reduces the goal to the right disjunct (В§10)\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that 3 is in the union of two sets. Since В§11,\n"
"the left set contains 3, so use В§12.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. В§13 вҖ” choose the left disjunct (3 is in the left set)\n"
"2. В§14 вҖ” unfold the set-builder membership\n"
"3. В§15 вҖ” close the arithmetic goal"
msgstr ""

