#: Game.Levels.ImageWorld.L08_ImageInterSubset
msgid "You proved В§0. Notice: only вҠҶ, not =.\n"
"\n"
"**Why equality fails**: The reverse inclusion В§1\n"
"would require: given witnesses В§2 and В§3 with\n"
"В§4, finding some В§5 with В§6.\n"
"But В§7 and В§8 might be DIFFERENT elements! There is no reason\n"
"that either one is in В§9.\n"
"\n"
"**The constant function counterexample**: Let В§10, В§11,\n"
"В§12:\n"
"- В§13 (witness: В§14 and В§15)\n"
"- В§16 (witness: В§17 and В§18)\n"
"- So В§19\n"
"- But В§20, so В§21\n"
"\n"
"The problem is that the witnesses are DIFFERENT (В§22 vs В§23). The\n"
"constant function collapses distinct inputs, creating intersections\n"
"in the image that do not correspond to intersections in the domain.\n"
"\n"
"**The witness transfer pattern**: Once again, the proof re-uses the\n"
"SAME witness В§24 from В§25. Since В§26 AND В§27, the same\n"
"witness works for both В§28 and В§29 simultaneously.\n"
"\n"
"**When does equality hold?** If В§30 is INJECTIVE, then the witnesses\n"
"must be the same (В§31), and equality holds.\n"
"You will prove this in Injective World.\n"
"\n"
"**The quantifier logic**: Why does union work but intersection fail?\n"
"Image membership is existential: В§32.\n"
"For union, the existential distributes: В§33 is\n"
"equivalent to В§34. One witness suffices\n"
"either way. For intersection, the existential does NOT distribute:\n"
"В§35 implies В§36, but NOT\n"
"the reverse -- the two existential witnesses might be different\n"
"elements. This is exactly the gap you just proved.\n"
"\n"
"**Updated scoreboard**:\n"
"\n"
"| Operation | Preimage | Image | Why? |\n"
"|---|---|---|---|\n"
"| В§37 (union) | = | = | В§38 distributes over В§39 |\n"
"| В§40 (intersection) | = | only вҠҶ | В§41 does NOT distribute over В§42 |\n"
"| В§43 (complement) | = | no relation | В§44 does not commute with В§45 in either direction: В§46 neither implies nor is implied by В§47 when В§48 is not injective |\n"
"\n"
"The library name is В§49."
msgstr ""

