msgid "You proved В§0.\n"
"\n"
"The key insight was the **contrapositive argument**: to show В§1,\n"
"you assumed В§2 and derived a contradiction via В§3.\n"
"This is the first time in this problem set that image membership was\n"
"used to DERIVE a contradiction rather than to BUILD a witness.\n"
"\n"
"**Why only \\\\subseteq**: The reverse В§4\n"
"does NOT hold. Consider В§5, В§6, В§7:\n"
"- В§8, so В§9\n"
"- В§10, В§11, so В§12\n"
"- В§13\n"
"\n"
"A non-injective function can map elements of В§14 to the same output\n"
"as elements of В§15, creating outputs in В§16 that\n"
"also appear in В§17.\n"
"\n"
"**The operations picture so far**:\n"
"\n"
"| Operation | Preimage | Image |\n"
"|---|---|---|\n"
"| Binary \\\\cap | = | only \\\\subseteq |\n"
"| Indexed \\\\bigcap | = | only \\\\subseteq |\n"
"| Binary \\\\cup | = | = |\n"
"| Indexed \\\\bigcup | = | = |\n"
"| Set difference \\\\ | = | only \\\\supseteq |\n"
"\n"
"Image does not preserve complement in either direction:\n"
"В§18 and В§19 have no inclusion relationship in general.\n"
"\n"
"**When does equality hold?** When В§20 is injective on В§21. If\n"
"different inputs always produce different outputs, no element of\n"
"В§22 can produce an output that also comes from В§23.\n"
"\n"
"The library name is В§24."
msgstr ""

