#: Game.Levels.IndexedOpsWorld.L09_VacuousIntersection
msgid "You proved that В§0 вҖ” intersecting over\n"
"an empty index gives everything.\n"
"\n"
"The key insight is **vacuous truth**: the statement В§1\n"
"is true because there are no В§2 to check. In Lean, В§3 is a type\n"
"with no constructors, so В§4 (equivalently, В§5)\n"
"discharges any goal about an element of В§6.\n"
"\n"
"**В§7 and В§8**: The pattern В§9 for В§10\n"
"is the type-level version of В§11 for В§12. Both say\n"
"\"from an impossible premise, anything follows\" вҖ” the principle of\n"
"explosion. You will see В§13 in propositional logic and\n"
"В§14 when working with uninhabited types (like В§15).\n"
"\n"
"**Why this is the right convention**: The intersection of a collection of\n"
"sets is the **largest set contained in all of them**. When the collection\n"
"is empty, every set is vacuously contained in all (zero) members of the\n"
"collection вҖ” so the largest such set is В§16. This is the same\n"
"pattern as:\n"
"- An empty product equals 1 (the multiplicative identity)\n"
"- An empty sum equals 0 (the additive identity)\n"
"- An empty conjunction (вҲҖ over nothing) is В§17\n"
"\n"
"In each case, the empty operation returns the **identity element** for\n"
"that operation. For intersection, the identity is В§18 (since\n"
"В§19 for all В§20). For union, the identity is В§21\n"
"(since В§22 for all В§23). This is why the dual result вҖ”\n"
"В§24 вҖ” is also true.\n"
"\n"
"**Why this matters**: This explains why **bounded** indexed intersections\n"
"(В§25) are needed. If В§26 might be empty, the bounded\n"
"intersection degenerates to В§27, which is often not what you\n"
"want. When you see a bounded intersection in a proof, always consider:\n"
"what happens if the bounding set is empty?\n"
"\n"
"**Up next**: You will prove the dual вҖ” В§28 вҖ”\n"
"completing the most dramatic duality pair in this world.\n"
"\n"
"In ordinary math: \"The intersection В§29\n"
"contains every element, because the defining condition вҖ” В§30\n"
"for all В§31 вҖ” is vacuously satisfied.\""
msgstr ""

