#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld
msgid "# Subset World\n"
"\n"
"In Set World, you learned that sets are predicates and membership is\n"
"predicate evaluation. Now you will learn the two fundamental\n"
"relationships between sets: **subset** (В§0) and **equality** (В§1).\n"
"\n"
"A **subset** proof В§2 means: for every element, if it is in В§3\n"
"then it is in В§4. The proof shape is always В§5 вҖ” fix an\n"
"element, assume it is in the smaller set, then show it is in the\n"
"larger set.\n"
"\n"
"A **set equality** proof В§6 means: the two sets have exactly the\n"
"same elements. There are two routes:\n"
"- **Extensionality** (В§7): prove В§8 directly\n"
"- **Double containment** (В§9): prove В§10 and\n"
"  В§11 separately\n"
"\n"
"By the end of this world, you will:\n"
"- Prove subset relations with the В§12 pattern\n"
"- Handle the boundary cases В§13 and В§14\n"
"- Use subset hypotheses as functions\n"
"- Disprove false subset claims by contradiction\n"
"- Chain subset proofs transitively\n"
"- Prove set equality via В§15 (extensionality)\n"
"- Prove set equality via В§16 (double containment)\n"
"- Prove set non-equality by finding a contradictory witness\n"
"- Prove proper subset (В§17) by combining В§18 and В§19\n"
"- Use В§20 to unwrap set notation on hypotheses\n"
"\n"
"You will also gain a new tactic (В§21) and a new proof strategy\n"
"(double containment) that you will use throughout the rest of this\n"
"course.\n"
"\n"
"**New tools in this world**:\n"
"- В§22 вҖ” unwrap a hypothesis to a definitionally equal form\n"
"- В§23 вҖ” reduce set equality to element-wise membership\n"
"- В§24 вҖ” derive equality from mutual subsets"
msgstr ""

