msgid "You just proved your first subset relation! The proof shape was:\n"
"\n"
"1. В§0 вҖ” introduce element and membership hypothesis\n"
"2. В§1 вҖ” extract the arithmetic from В§2\n"
"3. В§3 вҖ” unwrap the goal from set notation to arithmetic\n"
"4. В§4 вҖ” close the arithmetic goal\n"
"\n"
"This pattern вҖ” **intro, unwrap, prove** вҖ” is the standard shape for\n"
"every В§5 proof. The В§6 step is universal; the unwrapping\n"
"and closing steps depend on the specific sets.\n"
"\n"
"Using В§7 to extract hypothesis content works, but it is a bit\n"
"verbose вҖ” you need to write out the type explicitly. In the next\n"
"level, you will learn В§8, a tactic designed specifically for\n"
"this unwrapping job.\n"
"\n"
"**В§9 vs В§10 вҖ” a common confusion**: These are fundamentally different\n"
"relations. В§11 relates two *sets* and says every element of В§12\n"
"is also in В§13. В§14 relates an *element* and a *set* and says\n"
"В§15 belongs to В§16. In Lean, the types enforce this: В§17 requires\n"
"В§18, while В§19 requires В§20. If you are ever unsure,\n"
"check the types: are you relating two sets, or an element to a set?\n"
"\n"
