#: Game.Levels.SetOpsWorld.L12_PushNeg
msgid "# The push_neg Tactic\n"
"\n"
"When working with complements, you often encounter negated\n"
"propositions: В§0, В§1, В§2, etc.\n"
"You *could* break these apart manually, but there is a faster way.\n"
"\n"
"The В§3 tactic pushes negation through logical connectives\n"
"using standard equivalences:\n"
"\n"
"| Before push_neg | After push_neg |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| В§4 | В§5 |\n"
"| В§6 | В§7 |\n"
"| В§8 | В§9 |\n"
"| В§10 | В§11 |\n"
"\n"
"You can apply it to a hypothesis with В§12, or to the\n"
"goal with just В§13.\n"
"\n"
"**Your task**: Prove that the complement of a union is contained in\n"
"the intersection of the complements. This is one direction of\n"
"**De Morgan's law** for sets:\n"
"\n"
"В§14\n"
"\n"
"After В§15, you will have В§16, which is\n"
"definitionally В§17. Use В§18 to make the negated\n"
"disjunction explicit, then В§19 to convert it to\n"
"В§20 вҖ” which matches the goal.\n"
"\n"
"**Why В§21 is needed here**: Lean displays В§22\n"
"using set-theoretic complement notation, but В§23 needs to see\n"
"the negation explicitly as В§24. The tactic\n"
"В§25 converts to this definitionally\n"
"equal logical form so В§26 can process it. This\n"
"В§27 + В§28 pattern will recur whenever you work with\n"
"complements of compound sets."
msgstr ""

