#: Game.Levels.SubsetWorld.L14_Antisymm
msgid "В§0 gives you a one-step path from two вҠҶ proofs to\n"
"set equality. Compare the two routes:\n"
"\n"
"| Route | When to use |\n"
"|---|---|\n"
"| В§1 | When you need to prove both directions from scratch |\n"
"| В§2 | When you already have both вҠҶ proofs in hand |\n"
"\n"
"In practice, many set equality proofs start with В§3 because you\n"
"rarely have the subset proofs pre-packaged. But В§4 is\n"
"valuable when subset facts are available from other lemmas or\n"
"hypotheses.\n"
"\n"
"In ordinary math, this is the well-known principle: \"two sets are\n"
"equal iff each is a subset of the other.\" Every proof of set equality\n"
"by \"double inclusion\" (showing вҠҶ in both directions) is implicitly\n"
"using antisymmetry.\n"
"\n"
"A **partial order** is a relation that satisfies three properties:\n"
"1. **Reflexive**: В§5 for all В§6\n"
"2. **Transitive**: В§7 and В§8 imply В§9\n"
"3. **Antisymmetric**: В§10 and В§11 imply В§12\n"
"\n"
"You have now proved all three for В§13 on В§14:\n"
"- **Reflexive**: В§15 (Level 3)\n"
"- **Transitive**: В§16 (Level 8)\n"
"- **Antisymmetric**: В§17 (this level)\n"
"\n"
"Together, these make В§18 a **partial order** on sets. The partial\n"
"order concept is central to mathematics вҖ” you will study it in depth\n"
"in the Orders \\\\& Lattices course.\n"
"\n"
"These two routes вҖ” В§19 and В§20 вҖ” are logically *equivalent*.\n"
"You can derive В§21 from В§22 and В§23 from В§24. You\n"
"will prove this equivalence yourself in Levels 16 and 17."
msgstr ""

