#: Game.Levels.PreimageWorld.L14_PreimageComposition
msgid "# The Deepest Fact About Preimages\n"
"\n"
"You have proved that preimage preserves intersection, union,\n"
"complement, indexed unions, indexed intersections, and more. But\n"
"WHY does preimage preserve everything?\n"
"\n"
"The answer is one equation:\n"
"\n"
"В§0\n"
"\n"
"Preimage **reverses** function composition. If you compose В§1 after\n"
"В§2, then the preimage of В§3 is obtained by first taking the\n"
"preimage under В§4, then taking the preimage under В§5.\n"
"\n"
"This means preimage is just **composition on the predicate level**.\n"
"Since composition preserves all logical structure, preimage preserves\n"
"all set operations. That single fact explains every result in this\n"
"world.\n"
"\n"
"Notice the order reversal: В§6 applies В§7 first, then В§8. But\n"
"the preimage pulls back through В§9 first, then В§10. This is\n"
"called **contravariance** вҖ” preimage reverses the direction of\n"
"composition.\n"
"\n"
"**Proof plan**:\n"
"1. В§11 then В§12\n"
"2. Both directions: В§13 вҖ” the two sides are\n"
"   definitionally equal (both reduce to В§14)"
msgstr ""

